      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Yes, you have **real competitors**. Here's the landscape:\n\n---\n\n## Direct Competitors (same goal: universal session interchange)\n\n| Project | What it is | Readers (working) | Status | Threat level |\n|---------|-----------|-------------------|--------|-------------|\n| **AgentLog** (braintied/agentlog) | JSON format, Apache 2.0, 7 event types | Claude Code, Watchtower | Draft v0.2.0 | **Highest** — closest to your model, TypeScript ecosystem |\n| **ATIF** (harbor-framework) | JSON spec, academic-style RFC | MiniSweAgent, OpenHands, Gemini CLI | Proposed standard | **High** — multi-agent focused, has reference implementations |\n| **Agent Session Protocol** (kevin-dp) | JSONL format + `capi` CLI | Claude Code, Codex | Working | **High** — session *resume* (not just export), git-integrated |\n| **Unfirehose** (@unturf) | JSONL schema, OTel-compatible | Claude Code, Aider, Codex documented | v1.0 draft | **Medium** — covers more harnesses, but less depth |\n| **OTUTL** (clawRxiv paper) | JSON-Lines, academic | 4 vendors tested, 96.7% field coverage | Paper + validator | **Medium** — academic, replay-focused |\n| **.devsession** (reccli) | JSON with memory layers + terminal recording | Single tool | v1.1.0 | **Low** — narrower scope (one tool) |\n\n---\n\n## What they're building that you're also building:\n\n| Feature | You (AgentSON) | AgentLog | ATIF | Agent Session Protocol |\n|---------|---------------|----------|------|----------------------|\n| Cursor reader | Planned | Planned | Planned | No |\n| Cline reader | Planned | No | No | No |\n| Aider reader | Planned | Planned | No | No |\n| Claude Code | **Working** | **Working** | No | **Working** |\n| Codex | Planned | Planned | No | **Working** |\n| Gemini CLI | Planned | No | Documented | No |\n| Fine-tuning export | **Working** (Unsloth) | No | SFT pipeline | No |\n| Training data format | **Yes** | No | SFT/RL ready | No |\n| Cross-agent resume | No | No | No | **Yes** (unique) |\n\n---\n\n## Your advantages vs. theirs:\n\n1. **Fine-tuning export** — Nobody else has Unsloth/Olive integration. This is unique.\n2. **FreeStyle Libre 2 reader** — No one else covers health data. Unique niche.\n3. **SOP library** — 14 operational procedures. Nobody else has documentation depth.\n4. **Python ecosystem** — AgentLog is TypeScript-only. You have Python readers.\n\n## Their advantages vs. yours:\n\n1. **AgentLog** has OTel GenAI mapping (observability integration)\n2. **ATIF** has academic credibility (harbor-framework, RFC process)\n3. **Agent Session Protocol** can *resume* sessions cross-agent (you can only export)\n4. **Unfirehose** covers more harnesses in documentation\n\n---\n\n## The race for Cursor, Cline, Aider specifically:\n\nNobody has working readers for these yet. **It's a dead heat** — everyone has them as \"planned.\" First to ship wins mindshare. Your advantage: you already have 6 working readers and the pattern is proven. Their advantage: they have TypeScript ecosystems that Cursor/Cline users might prefer.\n\n**Bottom line:** You're not alone, but you're not behind. The differentiator is fine-tuning export (nobody else has it) and the healthcare angle (FreeStyle Libre). The risk is AgentLog — same Apache 2.0 license, same target audience, TypeScript ecosystem (which is where most AI tooling lives).",
      "timestamp": 1783287219986
