    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "**Watchtower** is Braintied's actual product. AgentLog is just the format they built for it.\n\n**What Watchtower does:**\n- Auto-captures your Claude Code sessions (via hooks)\n- AI-analyzes them (title, summary, category, key decisions)\n- Makes them searchable with semantic vector search (pgvector)\n- Stores in PostgreSQL\n\n**Their business model:**\n- Watchtower OSS = free, self-hosted, single project\n- **Ora Cloud** = paid enterprise version (multi-project, team mgmt, Slack digests, Sentry integration, AI cost tracking)\n\n**How big are they?**\n\n| | AgentLog | Watchtower |\n|---|---|---|\n| GitHub stars | 0 | 0 |\n| Commits | 9 | 3 |\n| Contributors | ~1-2 | ~1-2 |\n| npm packages | 1 (@braintied/agentlog) | 0 |\n| Releases | 2 (v0.1.0, v0.2.0) | 0 |\n| Paid product | No | Yes (Ora Cloud) |\n\n**They're tiny.** Both repos have 0 stars, 0 forks, 0 watchers. AgentLog has 9 commits. Watchtower has 3 commits. This is a very early-stage project — likely 1-2 people.\n\n**Their attention is split:**\n- AgentLog = spec/format work (the standard)\n- Watchtower = the actual product (where revenue comes from)\n- Ora Cloud = the enterprise version (where real money is)\n\n**What this means for you:**\n\nThey're not a serious threat right now. They have:\n- No working Cursor/Cline/Aider readers\n- No fine-tuning export\n- No Python SDK\n- No healthcare data\n- 0 stars on both repos\n\nTheir play is enterprise observability (Ora Cloud), not individual data ownership. They're building for engineering managers who want to track AI usage across teams. You're building for individual developers who want to own their data.\n\n**Different markets, different stories.**\n\nBut — if they get funded and start shipping readers fast, they could become a real competitor. The TypeScript ecosystem is where Cursor/Cline/Aider users live. If AgentLog becomes the de facto TypeScript standard for agent sessions, that's a problem.\n\n**Your window:** Ship Cursor, Cline, Aider readers before AgentLog does. They have them as \"planned.\" You have the pattern proven. Race is on.",
      "timestamp": 1783287471466
