      "text": "**50/51 tests pass.** The one failure is pre-existing in `test_claude_code.py` (not related to my changes). All 29 new tests pass.\n\nHere's what I built:\n\n## Three new readers — Cursor, Cline, Aider\n\n| Reader | Storage format | File | Tests |\n|--------|---------------|------|-------|\n| **cursor** | SQLite key-value (`state.vscdb`) | `readers/cursor.py` (310 lines) | 10 tests |\n| **cline** | JSON files (`api_conversation_history.json`) | `readers/cline.py` (265 lines) | 9 tests |\n| **aider** | Markdown (`.aider.chat.history.md`) | `readers/aider.py` (290 lines) | 10 tests |\n\n### What each reader does:\n\n**Cursor** — reads from `state.vscdb` (SQLite key-value store). Handles:\n- `composerData:` headers (session metadata)\n- `bubbleId:` entries (individual messages, type 1=user, 2=assistant)\n- Thinking/reasoning extraction\n- Tool results and tool-former data\n- Model name extraction from `modelInfo`\n\n**Cline** — reads from JSON files in `tasks/<ULID>/`. Handles:\n- `api_conversation_history.json` (primary source, Claude API format)\n- Content blocks: text, thinking, tool_use, tool_result\n- Task metadata (token usage, files in context)\n- Provider inference from model ID\n\n**Aider** — reads from `.aider.chat.history.md`. Handles:\n- Session splitting by `## [timestamp]` headers\n- Role parsing (`### User` / `### Assistant`)\n- Code block extraction and tool inference\n- SEARCH/REPLACE diff parsing\n\n### CLI updated:\n\n```bash\n# New tools available\nagentson export --tool cursor --all --output ./sessions/\nagentson export --tool cline --all --output ./sessions/\nagentson export --tool aider --all --output ./sessions/\nagentson list --tool cursor\nagentson list --tool cline\nagentson list --tool aider\n```\n\n### Your reader count:\n\n| Before | After |\n|--------|-------|\n| 6 readers | **9 readers** |\n| opencode, minimax, antigravity, libre, chrome_devtools, claude_code | + cursor, cline, aider |\n\nYou now cover **Tier 1 (Cursor)** and **Tier 2 (Cline, Aider)**. AgentLog still has 2 working readers. You're ahead 9-2.\n\nReady to commit and open PRs. Want me to do that?",
